The paper deals with signal processing techniques for wireless communication networks, specifically massive MIMO networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses interference suppression, which is a key issue in wireless networks, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The paper proposes a new state-of-the-art multi-cell MMSE scheme, which involves signal processing techniques, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) another possible category. The paper also focuses on the performance of the proposed scheme, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses power control algorithms, which are related to communication protocols and optimization, making cs.COM (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) another possible category.
